user.biography:
Welcome to the Salone del Mobile.Milano official Instagram profile.
The special event #supersalone21 will be held from 5th to 10th September 2021

node.text:
Il meglio dell'evoluzione del design e freneticamente accogliente. Di cosa stiamo parlando? Scopritelo nel nuovo video in collaborazione con @skytg24 con protagonisti @davideoldani @enricobertolino_ @stefano_boeri @claudia_segre 
#Salonedelmobile2021

node.text:
We won't stop. We can't stop. Salone del Mobile.Milano will be held from 16th to 21st June at Rho Fiera Milano, hear @BeppeSala, Mayor of #Milano, to know more
#SaloneDelMobile #SaloneDelMobile2020 #iSaloni #Eurocucina #SaloneDelBagno #ClaudioLuti #EmanueleOrsini

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 20, 2021. May be a closeup of 1 person.

node.text: “Our goal is a strong, united, inclusive, sustainable and creative Salone del Mobile,” says Maria Porro, newly-elected President of the Salone del Mobile.Milano, read more in the link in bio. Photo by @giovanni_gastel #mariaporro #thevoiceofsalone #salonedelmobile

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 18, 2021 tagging @samolineabeta. May be an image of 4 people, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
Bathrooms don't have to be the most colourless space in your home, don't be shy with colours and pop everything up!
Photos by Carola Merello, @baguray 
#SaloneDelMobile

node.text:
Do you think furnishing accessories are just plain and boring? Well think again, we have a whole zoo (and even dinosaurs!) today that will make you smile
Photos by Luca Fiammenghi, @baguray, @diegoravier 
#SaloneDelMobile

Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 16, 2021 tagging @studio_alexandrehumbert. May be an image of castle and outdoors.

node.text: Will the digital migration we are witnessing lead to an immaterial future? Alexandre Humbert from @studio_alexandrehumbert, designer-filmmaker with a philosophical attitude, wonders. Read more in the article by Marianna Guernieri, link in bio #salonedelmobile

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 16, 2021 tagging @studio_alexandrehumbert. May be an image of castle and outdoors.

Photo by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 16, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Objects are generators of emotions. Things that talk about the way we are. ALEXANDRE HUMBERT'.
Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 15, 2021 tagging @ivancarvalho_milan, and @m.sabetta. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'MARCO SABETTA'.

node.text: “We want to let the world know that Milan is not at a standstill, not ready to cede its place as the number one venue for talking about and purchasing design products” says @m.sabetta, General Manager of Salone del Mobile.Milano. Read more in the interview by @ivancarvalho_milan, link in bio #thevoiceofsalone #salonedelmobile

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 15, 2021 tagging @ivancarvalho_milan, and @m.sabetta. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'MARCO SABETTA'.

Photo by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'We have to remember that digital is important to facilitate the process of purchasing design products but it can't replace the experience one has when they are standing before an actual piece of design. MARCO SABETTA'.
Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 14, 2021 tagging @franpesca___, and @paolantonelli. May be a closeup of 1 person and text that says 'PAOLA ANTONELLI'.

node.text: The Salone, design beyond just furniture, new generations, fluidity: @paolantonelli, Senior Curator of the Department of Architecture and Design, as well as Director of R&D at MoMA. Read more in the article by @franpesca___  link in bio #speakerscorner #salonedelmobile

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 14, 2021 tagging @franpesca___, and @paolantonelli. May be a closeup of 1 person and text that says 'PAOLA ANTONELLI'.
Photo by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 14, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'For me, all design is political and social. PAOLA ANTONELLI'.
Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 13, 2021 tagging @magis_official, and @franpesca___. May be an image of 1 person, standing and text that says 'BARBARA MINETTO'.

node.text: The digital revolution and the eternal youth of the design world, the Salone as a moment of celebration and sustainability as a mindset. The wonderful world of @magis_official, straight to the point. Read more in the article by @franpesca___ link in bio #speakerscorner #salonedelmobile

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 13, 2021 tagging @magis_official, and @franpesca___. May be an image of 1 person, standing and text that says 'BARBARA MINETTO'.

Photo by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 13, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'I believe that a change of pace is fundamental today, or at least it should be. BARBARA MINETTO'.
Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 12, 2021 tagging @snaiderocucine. May be an image of kitchen.

node.text:
Add warmth to a kitchen with a versatile paint colour and some wood finishing
Photos by @baguray, @saverio_lombardi_vallauri 
#SaloneDelMobile

node.text: The Milanese designer @francescomeda focuses on design geared to purpose, less trend-led. He also explores art-design and self-production and takes his own particular approach to materials. Read more in the article by Patrizia Malfatti, link in bio #salonedelmobile

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 12, 2021 tagging @francescomeda. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'FRANCESCÓ RANC MEDA'.

Photo by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I hope companies and designers would be more sensitive when it comes to developing products that respond more fully to real needs and that they would use production processes, given that not all materials are finite. FRANCESCO MEDA'.
Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 10, 2021 tagging @porroofficial. May be an image of furniture and indoor.

node.text: Aside from the hackneyed diktat “less is more,” there’s a ‘light’ sort of design that doesn’t rely on addition but on subtraction, that doesn’t dumb down the concept but sits high on the crossroads of research and experimentation, where lightness is the outcome of a new balance of style, form and material. Read more in the article by Marilena Sobacchi, link in bio #designweekly #salonedelmobile
